WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:05.573
Welcome to Baria Temple International Church's Podcast.

00:06.855 --> 00:13.346
I am your host Timothy, and we're here together on this beautiful day to hear from God.

00:14.729 --> 00:20.579
So let's all prepare ourselves to receive what God has in store for us today.

00:22.182 --> 00:22.763
Let's begin.

00:24.245 --> 00:27.090
So we're going to continue on in our series.

00:27.554 --> 00:29.976
that we are working through.

00:30.036 --> 00:30.877
We are working through.

00:30.897 --> 00:34.381
If you can put it on the we are slide, guys, the sermon title.

00:34.401 --> 00:34.781
Thank you.

00:35.762 --> 00:42.849
We're gonna continue through this journey that we started two weeks ago called hope and healing for our community.

00:44.010 --> 00:46.553
We are, right?

00:46.933 --> 00:47.534
We are.

00:47.594 --> 00:51.157
We are going through who we are as a body.

00:51.297 --> 00:55.922
We are A.G. We are an Assemblies of God, spirit filled,

00:56.802 --> 00:58.504
Pentecostal church.

00:58.985 --> 01:02.009
We have a set of core doctrines that we all agree to.

01:02.430 --> 01:07.397
We have a set of beliefs that we all say, hey, this is what we're working towards.

01:08.218 --> 01:09.700
And that's all wonderful.

01:09.760 --> 01:12.144
And we spent our time going through those.

01:13.525 --> 01:25.362
But it doesn't matter what we believe, if we don't put what we believe into action, into actionable, tangible purposes.

01:26.690 --> 01:43.533
And so we believe that we are A.G. Church members, that we know what it is to be the body of Christ, to rise up and to stand up at the corner of Compton and Russell and say, we are the hands and feet of Jesus to this neighborhood.

01:46.097 --> 01:55.730
But beyond that, we are an A.G. Church who wants to offer hope and healing in our community.

01:56.066 --> 02:06.922
Listen, I can stand up here and I can preach to you the most glorious sermons of Babylon and the tabernacle and the temple and all of the rites and passages.

02:07.222 --> 02:11.889
I can give you all of the stories of Jesus and Ganesha and Galilee.

02:11.909 --> 02:18.418
And I can tell you all of the details and you can have all of the accumulated knowledge of the Scriptures.

02:20.098 --> 02:30.274
But if we do not put it into action, if we do not take that knowledge and share it outside of who we are, then what good is the knowledge?

02:31.677 --> 02:34.241
Well, I have it, I'm going to heaven, that's great, yay.

02:36.044 --> 02:41.232
But if we don't put it into action, we have to be a church of action.

02:42.874 --> 02:47.602
We have to be a church that can offer hope and healing to our community.

02:47.906 --> 02:57.637
So we're gonna turn our attention today to probably one of the most pervasive issues in our community specific.

02:58.758 --> 03:04.664
When we talk about our community, we're talking about South City, not St. Louis.

03:05.485 --> 03:10.190
Yes, St. Louis is our community, but we're talking about where does the church live?

03:11.071 --> 03:17.458
Now I know some of you live farther south than South County, some of you live in North City, some of you live in West County, whatever.

03:18.658 --> 03:23.629
But when we talk about the church home and where we live, we live in South City.

03:25.112 --> 03:39.122
And so when we talk about our community, we're talking about South City and what is one of the most pervasive issues that our city is dealing with today is the issue of fear.

03:41.602 --> 03:54.577
Whether it's the fear of rising crime in our neighborhoods, it's the fear or the fear, the anxiety of economic hardship that many families are facing or the uncertainty of the unknown in a rapidly changing world.

03:55.157 --> 03:58.862
Fear is something we all grapple with in different ways.

03:59.002 --> 04:04.608
Again, I want to express to you the importance of some of the images that I'm sharing with you.

04:04.688 --> 04:06.130
I'm not cherry picking.

04:06.594 --> 04:08.999
I went out to the St. Louis Post Dispatch.

04:09.360 --> 04:13.408
I picked the local articles and I screen-shotted that page.

04:13.448 --> 04:14.470
This was two weeks ago.

04:14.771 --> 04:16.935
Forgive me because we ended up doing VBS last week.

04:17.176 --> 04:18.338
So this was from two weeks ago.

04:18.779 --> 04:23.629
But this is the articles from our news for that day.

04:26.154 --> 04:28.018
All kinds of things that are happening.

04:28.258 --> 04:32.102
that we're dealing with fear in all kinds of way.

04:32.502 --> 04:38.688
Here in St. Louis, especially in our neighborhood, we see fears played out every day.

04:38.968 --> 04:58.226
The headlines remind us of challenges our community face, violence, job insecurity, food insecurity, the ongoing struggle for justice, equality, unity,

05:00.450 --> 05:02.874
These aren't just abstract concepts.

05:02.894 --> 05:09.844
They're not just ethereal things for us to think about and go, well, you know, they're real.

05:12.087 --> 05:25.047
They're pressing concerns that weigh heavily on the hearts and the minds of not only our citizenry, the people around us, but I would fair to say of some of us that are here in the building today.

05:26.589 --> 05:30.034
But as people of faith, we're called to respond

05:30.562 --> 05:31.163
to fear.

05:32.364 --> 05:37.830
We're called to respond to those who are in need, whatever the need is.

05:38.571 --> 05:49.423
Whatever is going on in our society, we are called to be the front line, the first responders, if you will, to the spiritual needs of our community.

05:52.307 --> 05:56.091
We're not recalled to respond to fear with despair.

05:56.892 --> 05:58.674
Oh, well, I'm so sorry.

05:59.554 --> 06:02.099
Oh man, yeah, that's horrible.

06:03.561 --> 06:06.366
But we need to respond with what we know.

06:06.426 --> 06:08.811
What do we know?

06:08.871 --> 06:10.854
We are.

06:12.337 --> 06:12.738
I am.

06:12.778 --> 06:14.842
He is who.

06:16.264 --> 06:18.027
So we are what?

06:18.468 --> 06:19.711
And if we are what?

06:19.771 --> 06:23.858
If we are, then we are the hands of feet of he who is.

06:24.130 --> 06:25.472
Do you see what I'm talking about?

06:25.513 --> 06:28.698
The building that we've been doing over the last year and a half.

06:28.718 --> 06:30.722
We understand who God is.

06:30.963 --> 06:39.378
So if we understand who God is and what that makes us, if he is Jehovah, Jaira, my provider,

06:40.002 --> 06:42.385
than we are ones who are provided for.

06:42.645 --> 06:46.470
We are ones who know how it is to be provided for.

06:46.490 --> 06:54.259
And so now today, we are ones who can take that provision out into the marketplace and say, I know you're going through struggles.

06:54.519 --> 06:56.361
I know you're going through difficulty.

06:56.622 --> 06:59.785
I know it's hard, but we serve a God who can answer.

07:02.949 --> 07:03.730
But do we?

07:04.898 --> 07:09.786
Do we take the answer out into the highways and byways into the marketplace?

07:11.990 --> 07:18.240
We are called to respond to fear with strength and assurance that God does provide.

07:20.804 --> 07:22.427
Wow, that should have got to name in, but that's okay.

07:24.370 --> 07:29.458
The Bible teaches us that faith is the antidote to fear.

07:30.210 --> 07:32.052
If we're fearful, we pray.

07:32.092 --> 07:34.615
If we're afraid, we seek God.

07:34.975 --> 07:38.819
If we are fearful about what's going on, we trust in the Lord.

07:39.560 --> 07:46.728
Faith offers us a way to live boldly and confidently even in the face of overwhelming obstacles.

07:48.049 --> 07:56.498
Listen, for some of you, you may be facing challenges that I will never understand, but also the reverse is true.

07:57.954 --> 08:01.277
I may be facing challenges with my family that you have no clue about.

08:04.000 --> 08:06.442
So today I want us to dig in.

08:06.482 --> 08:19.634
I want us to look at how our faith anchors us in God in his unshakable presence, how it strengthens us to act courageously and empowers us to bring hope and healing to our community.

08:19.895 --> 08:22.617
Because ultimately, that's what we're talking about.

08:22.657 --> 08:27.602
So today, if you're a note taker, our sermon title is overcoming

08:27.746 --> 08:29.048
fear with faith.

08:30.771 --> 08:34.477
Our community, how do we offer hope and healing to our community?

08:34.798 --> 08:47.179
We offer it by overcoming fear with faith, helping them see that there is an opportunity to serve a God who can provide and how overcome all that's going on.

08:47.439 --> 08:53.650
The first thing I want us to look at if you're a note-taker is that faith anchors us in God's presence.

08:55.746 --> 09:07.584
When fear begins to creep into our lives, it's easy to feel untethered, unconnected, as if we're being tossed by the waves of uncertainty, but we have an anchor.

09:11.049 --> 09:12.572
And that is our faith.

09:14.795 --> 09:18.901
There used to be a song, I forget who it was by, I think it was Ray Boltz, and said, the anchor holds.

09:20.564 --> 09:24.690
In the midst of the storm, the anchor holds.

09:25.218 --> 09:26.440
What is the anchor?

09:26.480 --> 09:27.261
It is our faith.

09:28.323 --> 09:30.186
It is our faith in our provider.

09:31.768 --> 09:36.556
It firmly grounds us in the unshakable presence of God.

09:36.876 --> 09:46.150
In the midst of the sea, in the midst of the turmoil, the ups and the downs of life, students, listen, you have no clue what you're about to get into.

09:47.573 --> 09:53.682
All of us who are adults, we can honestly tell you, and I think I can speak for almost every adult in the room.

09:54.530 --> 10:04.663
If we would have known at your age, the things that we were going to have to go through, I think we had to turn around and ran the other way.

10:06.085 --> 10:08.228
But you know what all of us have made, we've made it through.

10:08.268 --> 10:08.528
Why?

10:08.548 --> 10:09.009
How do I know that?

10:09.029 --> 10:09.770
Because we're all here today.

10:11.432 --> 10:13.955
Now, I'm not saying we don't have some bumps and bruises.

10:13.996 --> 10:15.497
I'm not saying we don't have some scars.

10:15.778 --> 10:18.962
I'm not saying that we don't have some internal heart hurt.

10:20.546 --> 10:24.351
that the Holy Spirit is still working on and dealing with and bringing us through.

10:24.632 --> 10:25.213
But you know what?

10:25.273 --> 10:25.994
We got through it.

10:26.054 --> 10:26.314
Why?

10:26.534 --> 10:28.718
Because our anchor holds.

10:30.380 --> 10:43.298
Our anchor is when we're in the midst of the sea, our anchor is connected to the bedrock down at the bottom of the sea, lodged in those things that aren't movable.

10:44.320 --> 10:48.786
And so when we anchor ourselves, when we anchor our faith in Christ,

10:49.378 --> 10:53.743
When we anchor our faith in Him, the wind and the waves can come.

10:53.803 --> 10:54.704
It doesn't matter.

10:57.448 --> 10:58.369
We'll write it out.

11:00.552 --> 11:04.376
Or he'll come and say, peace be still.

11:06.899 --> 11:15.390
And the trials and the tribulations all of a sudden doesn't mean that it's still, but the peace that passes understanding will come into our heart.

11:16.591 --> 11:18.994
And all of a sudden the wind and the waves, it doesn't matter.

11:20.578 --> 11:24.442
because I have a piece that nobody else can know about.

11:27.786 --> 11:31.991
See, this is a thing when we talk about peace and faith.

11:32.632 --> 11:38.038
It very often seems like it's distant or abstract, but it's not, it is real.

11:38.539 --> 11:39.460
It is abiding.

11:39.660 --> 11:44.445
It is something that we can depend on every day of our lives.

11:45.306 --> 11:48.530
It is not just an ethereal thought.

11:49.218 --> 11:53.324
Through our faith, we can recognize that God is with us.

11:57.349 --> 11:59.712
But we experience that peace when He is with us.

12:02.396 --> 12:07.863
And that sustains us in the midst of all that life will throw at you.

12:09.445 --> 12:10.487
Everything that comes.

12:15.413 --> 12:16.655
I want us to look a little bit.

12:16.675 --> 12:19.058
I want to take just a couple minutes in this particular

12:19.394 --> 12:24.241
main point to look at how anchoring works in our daily lives.

12:26.203 --> 12:40.523
Because when I was a student, when I was a younger person, I would hear my pastor talk about these abstract concepts, like, you know, crucify yourself daily.

12:41.844 --> 12:42.025
What?

12:42.065 --> 12:45.509
If I took that literal, what does that mean?

12:47.132 --> 12:48.914
Well, there's a cross.

12:50.338 --> 12:51.641
There's some nails downstairs.

12:52.343 --> 12:56.954
No, obviously it's an abstract concept to give up ourselves.

12:58.297 --> 13:08.562
And so I want to be practical about what it means to anchor ourselves in God's promises and the power of His prayer.

13:08.802 --> 13:12.766
So the first thing I want us to talk about is just simply God's promise to be with us.

13:12.786 --> 13:17.290
When we talk about anchoring ourselves, there is a promise that God has made to be with us.

13:17.390 --> 13:22.515
We look at Isaiah chapter 41 and verse 10, says, don't be afraid for I am with you.

13:22.815 --> 13:25.358
Don't be discouraged for I am your God.

13:25.758 --> 13:27.480
I will strengthen you and help you.

13:27.940 --> 13:31.664
I will hold you up with my victorious right hand.

13:32.605 --> 13:37.750
It doesn't say maybe it doesn't, there isn't any passivity to those statements.

13:37.810 --> 13:38.290
It says,

13:38.402 --> 13:42.588
Don't be afraid, I am with you.

13:44.111 --> 13:49.940
Not I might be, not I could be with you, I am with you.

13:50.461 --> 13:53.325
Don't be discouraged, I'm your God.

13:54.687 --> 13:56.249
Why do we have discouragement?

13:56.650 --> 14:04.402
Because we've placed something else in the place of God and now we're discouraged because it can't be God.

14:06.306 --> 14:12.836
If we're battling discouragement, it's because we've allowed something else to take the place of what God should have been.

14:12.896 --> 14:15.560
Does that make sense?

14:19.086 --> 14:21.670
He says, I will strengthen you and help you.

14:22.131 --> 14:22.551
I will.

14:24.494 --> 14:26.878
I will hold you up with my victorious right hand.

14:29.302 --> 14:31.986
In the face of fear,

14:32.738 --> 14:34.621
God's presence is our anchor.

14:35.061 --> 14:42.791
The promise that God is with us is powerful and it is a reminder that we're never alone, even in the most difficult situations.

14:43.292 --> 14:47.277
The presence is not passive, but active.

14:47.538 --> 14:52.364
He says, I will, I am present tense.

14:56.069 --> 14:59.634
God is with us to guide us, to protect us, and to provide for us.

15:01.250 --> 15:05.917
What does that mean to a South City St. Louis?

15:08.300 --> 15:09.102
You know what that tells me?

15:11.024 --> 15:17.614
With fear abiding in South City tells me that God isn't in the place that He needs to be.

15:19.156 --> 15:20.258
And whose fault is that?

15:23.623 --> 15:25.746
How many churches are in South City?

15:27.618 --> 15:34.409
How many churches that will even exclude the ones that are fringe or we would call off base?

15:35.611 --> 15:53.842
How many Bible believing, God fearing, Pentecostal, Baptist, non-denominational, whatever evangelical, EV free churches are in South City and yet fear runs rampant in our city?

15:55.458 --> 15:57.060
People are afraid to go outside.

15:57.160 --> 15:59.382
People are afraid to walk their dogs.

15:59.462 --> 16:02.345
People are afraid to go to the gas station in the evenings.

16:07.451 --> 16:09.153
But see, there's something that can happen.

16:10.214 --> 16:11.355
That we is the church.

16:11.675 --> 16:13.457
And this is only a first step.

16:15.199 --> 16:18.022
See, we can help our city find peace through prayer.

16:19.884 --> 16:21.586
We can be praying for our city.

16:24.130 --> 16:27.774
who prays specifically for the city.

16:28.795 --> 16:30.736
Not talking about in general, Lord, bless the city.

16:30.877 --> 16:44.009
I'm talking about Lord, bless Compton Heights, bless Shaw, bless Fox Park, bless Sullard, Lord, have your way over Tower Grove East.

16:44.249 --> 16:48.474
Lord, let your Holy Spirit come and move over the Grove.

16:51.516 --> 16:53.138
Specific your neighborhood,

16:53.282 --> 17:00.910
by name and to begin to cry out to the Holy Spirit, to pour himself over our neighborhood.

17:00.950 --> 17:07.977
I can tell you, we do on a semi-regular basis as a board, pray for our city.

17:10.500 --> 17:20.370
And specifically, we've taken up at our last board meeting to pray specifically for Compton Heights, our neighborhood, our home.

17:23.138 --> 17:31.271
Philippians chapter four, verses six and seven, this should be a very familiar passage says, don't worry about anything.

17:31.551 --> 17:32.212
Say anything.

17:33.514 --> 17:36.539
Instead, pray about everything.

17:36.880 --> 17:40.786
Tell God what you need and thank Him for all that He has done.

17:41.378 --> 17:46.285
Then you will experience God's peace, which exceeds anything we can understand.

17:46.565 --> 17:51.172
His peace will guard your hearts and minds as you live in Christ Jesus.

17:51.572 --> 17:54.817
Prayer is our lifeline to God's peace.

17:57.961 --> 18:07.314
When fear grips our hearts, we're invited to bring our anxieties to the Lord.

18:08.994 --> 18:18.946
And he graciously exchanges our fear, our anxiety, our worry for his peace.

18:22.210 --> 18:32.882
We need to take that message to the lost and dying of South City, of North City, of South County, of West County, of North County,

18:35.202 --> 18:40.969
See, this is our Jerusalem and Judea and Samaria into the uttermost parts of the earth.

18:42.070 --> 18:45.113
Our Jerusalem, yes, we live in a metropolitan area.

18:45.394 --> 18:50.379
So I would, I would posit to you that our Jerusalem is not St. Louis.

18:50.720 --> 18:56.786
Our Jerusalem is South City or maybe even more specifically Compton Heights.

18:58.729 --> 19:03.474
And then we move out from there and out from there and out from there.

19:05.730 --> 19:15.826
And so as we exist as a church, we need to find ourselves anchored in God, in His peace.

19:16.227 --> 19:26.002
When we find ourselves anchored in God's presence, we find peace through our faith, and then we are able to then share that peace

19:26.274 --> 19:27.095
with others.

19:27.455 --> 19:39.387
If we don't have peace, if we are not anchored, if we are still being tossed to and fro through all of the life's storms, then we have nothing to offer to the lost and the dying.

19:39.407 --> 19:46.233
There is no lifesaver ring to throw out to somebody else who's out there being tossed to and fro.

19:48.255 --> 19:55.282
But if we're in the boat, if we're anchored and we're solid and we're stable and we can say, Hey over here!

19:57.154 --> 19:57.775
Catch this.

20:02.700 --> 20:04.282
We can begin to help pull them in.

20:05.203 --> 20:07.906
See, that's a weird analogy, but it's evangelism.

20:08.406 --> 20:09.788
It's really all evangelism is.

20:10.869 --> 20:13.992
It's taking a lifeline and sharing it with somebody else.

20:15.114 --> 20:18.137
It's taking a lifeline and saying, I have the answer.

20:19.859 --> 20:26.546
How many of us, if we were out on the water and we saw somebody drowning and they were going on to

20:28.290 --> 20:28.691
Blah.

20:30.193 --> 20:32.596
And we had a life jacket sitting right here.

20:34.659 --> 20:35.540
How many of us would go?

20:35.560 --> 20:42.510
Of course not.

20:43.852 --> 20:45.654
Yet, how we treat evangelism.

20:46.435 --> 20:48.198
That's how we treat sharing our faith.

20:50.181 --> 20:51.543
God, well, Lord bless them.

20:52.103 --> 20:54.066
Somebody will tell them about Jesus, I'm sure.

20:54.402 --> 21:00.909
All the while he's going, hey, listen, I just stacked you up with a whole bunch of life jackets, a whole bunch of life rings.

21:09.720 --> 21:13.744
See, when we talk about faith that anchors us, it also empowers us.

21:14.745 --> 21:22.354
It gives us the strength and the courage to step out and to take action, even when the fear tries to hold us back.

21:22.434 --> 21:23.455
What are they going to say?

21:23.536 --> 21:25.098
Are they going to make fun of me students?

21:25.138 --> 21:26.940
This is an important one for you.

21:27.421 --> 21:30.405
You know, I don't want to, I don't want to not be the cool kid.

21:30.425 --> 21:32.088
I don't want to not be popular.

21:32.148 --> 21:33.910
I don't want to not be this or that.

21:34.251 --> 21:40.540
And so I don't want to say nothing about my faith because well, you know, I told dirty jokes or I cussed a whole bunch yesterday.

21:40.600 --> 21:43.765
And then if I tried to tell Jesus today, what are people going to think?

21:43.785 --> 21:47.570
They're just going to think I'm a hypocrite or they're not going to buy in or whatever it is.

21:50.466 --> 21:59.340
but we're called to share our faith, we're called to step out and to take action, even in the midst of difficulties.

22:02.665 --> 22:19.090
So our faith keeps us grounded, but also pushes us forward to act courageously, even in the face of fear, even in the face of the stuff that's going on, but then faith for us strengthens us to act accordingly.

22:20.034 --> 22:21.196
So this is number two, guys.

22:27.444 --> 22:30.048
Faith strengthens us to act courageously.

22:31.390 --> 22:38.920
When we talk about offering hope and healing to our community, this is not something we can do lightly.

22:38.960 --> 22:42.305
It's not something that we can do just flippantly.

22:42.545 --> 22:48.754
And frankly, it's not something we typically do instinctively or comfortably.

22:49.858 --> 22:56.365
Typically, for us, stepping out means that we have to step out in faith, stepping out with courage.

22:56.826 --> 23:02.072
Faith provides us the comfort of God's presence, but it also demands something more.

23:02.352 --> 23:04.154
It calls us to action.

23:06.176 --> 23:07.818
True faith is never stagnant.

23:07.838 --> 23:18.610
It never stirs us within us without giving us the courage to face our fears head on and to take the step that reflects our trust in God.

23:20.770 --> 23:22.011
What does Acts 1, 8 say?

23:22.652 --> 23:23.513
It says, you'll receive.

23:23.533 --> 23:27.237
Oh, come on.

23:27.257 --> 23:28.038
We will receive.

23:28.058 --> 23:31.402
This is, we are assemblies of God.

23:31.482 --> 23:34.786
This is probably our foundation of verse.

23:35.867 --> 23:41.974
You will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes upon you to be what?

23:42.215 --> 23:43.136
My witness.

23:43.236 --> 23:45.138
This is what we're talking about.

23:45.218 --> 23:48.603
faith gives us the strength to step out.

23:48.904 --> 24:00.642
Courage is not something we muster on our own, but it is strength given by God, by the Holy Spirit, enabling us to act even when we feel uncertain, even when we don't feel like doing it.

24:01.062 --> 24:05.449
In this way, not only our faith not only reassures us, but equips us.

24:07.352 --> 24:08.754
You'll be my witnesses.

24:09.026 --> 24:20.851
You'll be received power to be a witness, the equipping of that power, the equipping to be the witness's power, strength, courage, faith, to share what it is that we need to share.

24:20.911 --> 24:24.338
And this is who we are as the church.

24:24.482 --> 24:27.367
It gives us the ability to take steps of faith.

24:27.507 --> 24:31.314
Joshua chapter one in verse nine says, this is my command.

24:31.354 --> 24:34.138
Be strong and courageous.

24:34.158 --> 24:39.547
Do not be afraid or discouraged for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.

24:42.873 --> 24:44.656
Be strong and courageous.

24:46.299 --> 24:47.040
Don't be afraid.

24:47.100 --> 24:48.242
Don't be discouraged.

24:50.434 --> 24:54.599
Faith isn't merely believing, but it is acting on that belief.

24:55.320 --> 25:06.193
God calls us to be strong and courageous, knowing that his presence empowers us to step out in faith, even when we feel maybe a little bit of that fear.

25:10.118 --> 25:14.163
You see, Peter was called out to take a literal step of faith out of the boat.

25:15.104 --> 25:20.210
That kind of faith took courage that was outside of Peter's normal ability.

25:20.866 --> 25:21.687
How do we know that?

25:21.747 --> 25:26.391
Because almost immediately he puts his eyes on the water and begins to sink.

25:26.812 --> 25:44.428
But in that moment, Jesus reached his hand out to save him, showing that even if our courage is a bit shaky, even if our courage isn't a hundred percent, Jesus, God, the Holy Spirit is there to support us.

25:45.129 --> 25:50.514
Even if what God is calling us to seems daunting, his presence will sustain us.

25:52.130 --> 25:58.418
Even if it seems ridiculous, Peter, I need you to step out of the boat and onto the water.

25:58.438 --> 25:59.560
Peter was a fisherman.

25:59.660 --> 26:00.762
He knew what that meant.

26:01.923 --> 26:06.049
Peter knew as soon as I put my foot on the water, it's gonna go down through the water.

26:06.329 --> 26:09.553
They weren't super great on science at that point, but guess what?

26:09.974 --> 26:12.357
He understood surface tension.

26:14.019 --> 26:22.130
It wasn't gonna happen, but in spite of his fear, he said, I see you, Lord.

26:22.658 --> 26:24.560
My eye is anchored on you.

26:25.021 --> 26:27.503
My faith is anchored in you.

26:27.864 --> 26:31.127
And if you have called me out, I'm gonna take this step.

26:32.088 --> 26:33.290
I don't understand it.

26:33.910 --> 26:40.778
I know the reality of what's gonna happen, but I'm gonna do it anyway because my eyes aren't on the water, my eyes are on you.

26:42.680 --> 26:43.921
And he took the step of faith.

26:44.702 --> 26:46.985
Now, he's human, he's not Jesus.

26:48.666 --> 26:49.988
All of a sudden he went, okay, I did it.

26:51.029 --> 26:51.890
Wait, what did I do?

26:53.474 --> 26:55.717
Uh oh, and he began to sink.

26:57.439 --> 26:59.321
And Jesus was like, ah, come on.

27:02.065 --> 27:02.946
And he pulls him back out.

27:06.891 --> 27:08.193
What does this look like for the church?

27:09.995 --> 27:12.398
What does this look like for Berea Temple?

27:15.041 --> 27:17.685
This might be getting involved in community initiatives.

27:18.426 --> 27:21.810
Things that we typically aren't, you know, super involved in.

27:23.906 --> 27:33.398
It might be creating a ministry to support those in need or it might be standing up for what's right.

27:35.521 --> 27:40.227
It might be being the literal hands and feet of Jesus.

27:44.132 --> 27:52.402
Getting out, getting up out of our seat, walking out the doors and begin walking down the street to go, okay, Lord,

27:53.474 --> 27:56.597
So how many of you remember the Seek and Save event last year?

27:57.558 --> 27:59.460
Hopefully everybody, it's not been that long ago.

28:01.522 --> 28:15.756
The young man that we had speak that day, our guest speaker, I follow him on Facebook and they do this thing like or not like the name of it, but they do what they call miracle hunting.

28:16.777 --> 28:21.362
And their church goes out on the weekends and they begin

28:21.538 --> 28:34.379
They pray over a section of neighborhood, and they begin to go and walk that neighborhood looking for what God is gonna do in that neighborhood, and they begin to pray.

28:34.820 --> 28:47.922
And in that process, they have baptized people, they have led people to Christ, they have cast out demons, they have healed people, they have seen miracles happen because their faith was anchored.

28:49.250 --> 28:52.673
And it may mean that some of us who go, what?

28:53.694 --> 28:54.815
You want us to do what?

28:57.978 --> 29:02.042
May need to come together at, oh, I don't know, what do we do on Wednesday nights?

29:04.244 --> 29:05.025
We have prayer meeting.

29:06.246 --> 29:08.528
And at prayer meeting, we could do what?

29:09.409 --> 29:19.218
Pray and begin to pray over neighborhoods and then take not just here, but then take action

29:19.490 --> 29:38.011
and move beyond these four walls and take that prayer time and move out into the community, out into the neighborhood as a concerted effort that we are the hands and feet of Jesus to a lost and dying world who are going to provide hope and healing to our community.

29:39.112 --> 29:44.178
And we're going to go on miracle hunting adventures or

29:45.794 --> 29:49.578
Christ interaction, divine appointment, whatever we want to call it.

29:49.978 --> 29:51.400
I'm not saying we have to do that.

29:51.460 --> 29:55.464
I'm simply saying, what might that look like as a church?

29:57.205 --> 30:08.257
Putting into practice overcoming fear with faith and taking a step of faith beyond who we are and what we are right now.

30:08.597 --> 30:13.682
Because the church is the source of courage.

30:13.794 --> 30:16.259
Christ is the source, but what is the church?

30:16.319 --> 30:18.724
The church is the hands and feet of Jesus.

30:18.744 --> 30:28.123
2 Timothy chapter 1 and verse 7 says, for God has not given us a spirit of fear and timidity, but of power, love, and self-discipline.

30:29.105 --> 30:35.378
He has given us power, love, and self-discipline, not fear.

30:36.514 --> 30:43.222
we can step out and take that power and express the love of Jesus to a lost and dying world.

30:43.642 --> 30:53.674
We have to take the self-discipline step to step out, or we'll never be a church that offers hope and healing to our community.

30:53.934 --> 31:00.402
The Holy Spirit is with us in His power.

31:00.546 --> 31:03.069
He has the ability to create things.

31:03.470 --> 31:23.215
He has the ability to bring people together and say, I don't care what color you are, I don't care what background you are, what nation you come from, or what your socioeconomic status is, but he can bring them together in a single unified body, and we can move forward together as a body.

31:23.235 --> 31:24.116
How do I know this?

31:24.196 --> 31:25.678
Because we have already done it.

31:27.260 --> 31:28.882
He has already done it.

31:30.818 --> 31:32.922
And so what do we as a church?

31:34.445 --> 31:35.948
What are we called to be?

31:36.028 --> 31:40.778
We are called to be the hands and feet of Jesus, to do what?

31:41.078 --> 31:44.385
To seek and to save that which is lost.

31:45.948 --> 31:50.617
We are hunters, not in a masculine pseudo thing.

31:50.938 --> 31:53.202
We are for Christ.

31:53.666 --> 32:05.362
on a mission to find those who are lost, to seek them out, to find them, and to provide an opportunity, a pathway back to Christ for them.

32:08.610 --> 32:16.464
We are not just individuals, but a community empowered by God to be a source of courage for each other and for our community.

32:16.724 --> 32:31.250
When our community is having a difficulty, I was asked one day, would Berea Temple, if there was a shooting in the neighborhood or in the vicinity, would Berea Temple be willing to open their doors as a

32:31.298 --> 32:37.567
a resource as a meeting place, a place of refuge so that they could meet and come and be here.

32:37.587 --> 32:39.089
I said, absolutely call me.

32:40.171 --> 32:42.774
I said, I will fling open the doors as wide as they can.

32:44.977 --> 32:46.359
Are we ready for that though?

32:46.920 --> 32:52.708
Do we have people who said, hey, Pastor, I know it's a few and far between thing, but I'm ready.

32:52.869 --> 32:56.333
I'm equipped, Pastor, I want you to know I have a background in.

32:56.394 --> 32:59.538
And if that happens, call me.

32:59.970 --> 33:00.591
I will be here.

33:00.611 --> 33:01.592
I don't care what time it is.

33:01.612 --> 33:05.298
I will be there to help and lend whatever hand I can.

33:05.618 --> 33:10.085
And maybe that's simply filling water jugs and bringing up fresh water for people to drink.

33:12.929 --> 33:18.738
Maybe it's offering help to triage for our understaffed police officers and EMS workers.

33:19.018 --> 33:20.080
And you're a medical person.

33:20.280 --> 33:22.904
And you're like, hey, listen, I'm already licensed equipped.

33:22.924 --> 33:24.146
I already know what to do.

33:25.922 --> 33:27.103
But see, these are ministries.

33:27.163 --> 33:30.507
These are opportunities to be the hands and feet of Jesus.

33:34.330 --> 33:46.763
When we gather, when we pray, when we work together, we encourage each other to face our own fears and to face the issues that are going on with our community, together with boldness.

33:47.103 --> 33:53.810
When our faith strengthens us to act courageously, we'll see that our actions are not just for our benefit.

33:53.922 --> 34:01.256
When we talk about being anchored in Christ here in our hearts, it's going to automatically have an outflow.

34:01.517 --> 34:03.421
It's going to impact those around us.

34:03.521 --> 34:06.126
It's going to help us find courage that comes from faith.

34:06.386 --> 34:13.701
It is not only for our personal victories, but intended to bring about a transformation for our community.

34:14.622 --> 34:16.466
God is equipping us.

34:16.770 --> 34:18.196
for our community.

34:18.457 --> 34:23.239
He is making changes in me today for our community.

34:23.480 --> 34:25.810
He is making changes in you

34:25.954 --> 34:29.578
for something that he has planned for the community.

34:29.598 --> 34:34.643
And you're not gonna be the same Christian that you are today, that you were yesterday.

34:34.864 --> 34:39.449
Because who you were yesterday was for his plan and purpose yesterday.

34:39.689 --> 34:45.855
Who you were 10 years ago was to serve a purpose that he had for this church 10 years ago.

34:46.156 --> 34:48.178
But he has a new plan, a new purpose.

34:48.198 --> 34:52.923
When I got here, we talked about, we sang about new wine, new wine skins.

34:53.243 --> 34:55.666
There is a new plan, a new purpose, a new

34:55.746 --> 34:57.288
function of what we're doing.

34:58.570 --> 35:12.508
And he is equipping each one of us for this next phase of what he wants to do, not at Berea Temple, not only at Berea Temple, but within the city, within the community that we serve.

35:17.894 --> 35:23.762
But how do we bring faith and power and hope and healing to the world around us?

35:25.570 --> 35:29.015
faith empowers us to transform our community.

35:30.697 --> 35:41.231
Listen, when we talk about offering hope and healing, we're talking about transformation, we're talking about change, we're talking about a fundamental shift.

35:43.594 --> 35:49.442
I know those of you who have been at Brea Temple for forever, you already know this, but I'm just gonna make it as a general statement anyway.

35:51.605 --> 35:52.626
Essentially,

35:52.994 --> 36:04.410
At its core, I know there's some apartment owners and things that are maybe a little more, but Berea Temple is the largest anchor organization in Compton Heights.

36:05.592 --> 36:07.835
We are the center of the community.

36:08.897 --> 36:21.074
Within our actual little neighborhood boundaries, our church, I mean, there was a church that used to be down there that was the literature museum, but it's long since gone.

36:22.434 --> 36:26.579
We may not be numerically, but we sit as the core of this neighborhood.

36:28.141 --> 36:32.947
We have an opportunity to be the center of the neighborhood again.

36:34.408 --> 36:36.711
When people talk about, I need help.

36:37.252 --> 36:38.834
Where do they, where do we want them to go?

36:39.515 --> 36:40.976
We want them to come knock on the doors.

36:41.036 --> 36:42.338
We don't want them to go to the city.

36:43.139 --> 36:52.370
We don't want them to go to some who's going to just put them into some system and they're going to be in number and then we want them to knock on our doors.

36:53.058 --> 36:54.399
We want to be the first stop.

36:55.160 --> 36:56.722
When somebody says, hey, you know what?

36:56.742 --> 36:57.703
I'm going through something.

36:59.285 --> 36:59.985
I want us to pray.

37:00.106 --> 37:06.893
I told you the story of the man, the homeless gentleman who found his way in through an unlocked door by accident and was sitting.

37:07.994 --> 37:08.875
That doesn't bother me.

37:09.956 --> 37:13.760
I mean, I understand there's some safety concerns and things like that.

37:15.282 --> 37:22.930
But I want people to know that this is a place of refuge, a place of sanctuary, where they can come

37:23.554 --> 37:30.361
Regardless if they're a member or not, I told you about the sign outside, there's hope change can happen.

37:30.381 --> 37:32.804
The last line says, join us Sunday.

37:34.265 --> 37:34.806
Join us.

37:36.027 --> 37:38.470
Come, be a part of what there is.

37:41.913 --> 37:44.596
We can be empowered to change our community.

37:44.897 --> 37:47.720
We can become agents of change.

37:47.740 --> 37:50.002
Look at Matthew chapter five and verse 14.

37:51.554 --> 37:53.618
Verse 14 through verse 16.

37:54.082 --> 37:58.686
says, you are the light of the world like a city on a hilltop that cannot be hidden.

37:59.146 --> 38:02.329
No one lights a lamp and then puts it under a basket.

38:02.369 --> 38:07.454
Instead, a lamp is placed on a stand where it gives light to everyone in the house.

38:07.734 --> 38:14.199
In the same way, let your good deeds shine out for all to see so that everyone will praise your heavenly Father.

38:14.460 --> 38:20.145
Berea Temple stands at the pinnacle, at the corner, at the center of Compton Heights.

38:20.485 --> 38:22.246
We don't want that to be hidden.

38:22.487 --> 38:24.068
We want to put it up on the

38:24.048 --> 38:27.452
lamp stand as it is, and where everybody can see.

38:27.712 --> 38:29.234
Everybody drives by here.

38:29.554 --> 38:34.059
I talk to people out in the community all of the time, and I'm not talking about this community.

38:34.099 --> 38:47.174
I'm talking about just in my out and abouts, and people say, it'll come up that I'm a pastor of one of the churches here in the city, and they'll go, oh, really, we're at, and I'll say, Berea Temple is international church, and they'll go, oh, where's that at?

38:47.234 --> 38:48.936
Well, we're at the corner of Compton and Russell.

38:49.317 --> 38:51.159
Oh, I drive by there every day.

38:52.460 --> 38:54.002
Literally, all the time.

38:54.114 --> 38:55.135
regular occurrence.

38:55.736 --> 38:56.978
I drive by there all the time.

38:58.139 --> 38:59.441
I drive by there on my way to work.

38:59.481 --> 39:01.684
I drive by there on my way to this or that or whatever.

39:04.268 --> 39:06.651
Now sometimes it's, oh, we didn't know that church was still open.

39:08.333 --> 39:09.214
Yes, it's still open.

39:11.558 --> 39:15.283
Most of the time they go, oh yeah, we've seen that church.

39:15.303 --> 39:17.766
So then my response usually is, well, then you should come inside.

39:19.048 --> 39:19.949
We would love to have you.

39:19.969 --> 39:23.634
We'd love for you to visit and come and be part of what we're doing.

39:27.202 --> 39:29.365
We as the church can be agents of change.

39:30.967 --> 39:33.811
We can be the thing, the catalyst.

39:33.831 --> 39:38.778
When we talk about wanting to see change in St. Louis, we can be it.

39:39.839 --> 39:42.122
It only took 12 to change the known world.

39:44.065 --> 39:47.329
Yeah, disciples, 12 of them, remember that Sunday school?

39:48.190 --> 39:48.290
Okay.

39:48.310 --> 39:49.953
If not, teach that next week.

39:49.973 --> 39:50.353
I'm kidding.

39:50.373 --> 39:57.042
There's, I don't know how many people in the room today.

39:57.506 --> 39:58.267
There's more than 12.

40:00.690 --> 40:08.479
We can be agents of change for changing South City, changing the makeup, changing the heart of the city.

40:10.902 --> 40:14.125
We are Berea Temple, a church with a heart for the city.

40:15.066 --> 40:15.847
Why do I know that?

40:16.548 --> 40:19.892
Because I found letterhead in the church office that has that printed on it.

40:20.553 --> 40:24.978
Said, Berea Temple, a church in the heart of the city with a heart for the city.

40:27.170 --> 40:27.851
And I like that.

40:29.612 --> 40:30.593
That's who we need to be.

40:31.474 --> 40:33.616
We need to have a heart for the city.

40:35.558 --> 40:40.403
Because fear is going to paralyze our community, and it has in many ways.

40:41.424 --> 40:43.726
But faith can mobilize it.

40:44.026 --> 40:52.455
When we talk about seek and save, that was faith mobilizing people to make an impact in our neighborhood.

40:54.136 --> 40:55.858
As believers, we're called

40:56.386 --> 40:58.209
to be light in dark places.

40:59.551 --> 41:00.692
Can I tell you a little secret?

41:00.732 --> 41:01.714
How many of you have heard that before?

41:01.734 --> 41:04.238
We're called to be light in the midst of the dark, right?

41:04.819 --> 41:05.580
You've heard that before.

41:05.600 --> 41:07.483
You know what that means?

41:08.805 --> 41:10.868
It means you have to go into dark places.

41:11.869 --> 41:13.151
Most of us don't like that.

41:14.133 --> 41:23.186
Most of us, when we enter a room, we go, click, light, because we don't want to be in the dark, sometimes even in our own homes.

41:24.610 --> 41:28.896
But to be light in dark places means we have to go to dark places.

41:30.498 --> 41:37.267
To bring hope and healing to areas that are plagued by fear, we have to be willing to step out.

41:37.527 --> 41:44.817
We have to be like our ancestors and run into the pro-leg into the problem and offer hope and healing, not run away from it.

41:47.480 --> 41:48.882
One of our sister churches,

41:52.770 --> 41:54.312
And you've heard me talk a lot about this.

41:54.393 --> 42:04.649
But one of our sister AG churches, Life 360 in Springfield, many years ago, created a nonprofit to address the needs of their community beyond what the church could normally do.

42:04.689 --> 42:11.099
Today, they have food distribution programs across the state and to rural communities.

42:11.380 --> 42:12.882
They're helping create jobs.

42:14.818 --> 42:24.389
and they have transitional housing for those that age out of the foster care system, helping them find stability and many other areas within their lives.

42:25.331 --> 42:33.240
These are the type of things that are possible when we overcome fear with faith and believe that we can become agents of change.

42:33.801 --> 42:35.383
These are the things that can happen.

42:35.643 --> 42:37.946
You look at those numbers that were shared.

42:38.867 --> 42:41.490
Specifically, I can't read those from over here.

42:41.762 --> 42:50.913
748,885 meals served, 25 communities reached, 54 new jobs created.

42:54.377 --> 42:57.601
They had faith to step out and say, listen, I think we can do this.

42:58.923 --> 43:07.954
We may or may not have the ability within our own pocketbook today, but I believe that we can step out in faith and do this.

43:09.794 --> 43:12.036
We can be the agents of change.

43:12.737 --> 43:24.329
Now for us, whether that's simply doing community outreach, advocacy for justice, or simply loving our neighbors, our faith should be evident in all of our actions.

43:28.033 --> 43:32.558
The last thing I want us to share is just, it's a rubber meets the road kind of a thing.

43:33.679 --> 43:36.242
It's just a practical down to earth.

43:37.922 --> 43:40.845
The only way we're going to restore hope is through faithful living.

43:42.567 --> 43:44.089
We have to be found faithful.

43:46.392 --> 43:52.999
It's great to talk and champion and cheer about all those things that are going on and all of these wonderful things.

43:54.001 --> 43:59.647
But if we don't restore our own faithful living, we have no opportunity.

43:59.667 --> 44:03.171
Again, we have nothing to throw as a lifeline.

44:03.271 --> 44:05.554
Look at Romans chapter 15 and verse 13.

44:06.530 --> 44:13.941
says, I pray that God, the source of hope, fill you completely with joy and peace because you trust in Him.

44:14.622 --> 44:20.230
Then you will overflow with confident hope through the power of the Holy Spirit.

44:20.250 --> 44:28.882
There's a lot of people that I see that claim to be in Christ who appear to be running on about half empty.

44:30.530 --> 44:31.791
And so there's no overflow.

44:31.811 --> 44:33.233
It's not that they don't have some.

44:33.273 --> 44:39.879
It's not that they're not somewhat filled, but there is no overflow.

44:41.100 --> 44:42.722
There is no outflow.

44:44.624 --> 44:47.046
See, our faith is not just for ourselves.

44:47.086 --> 44:48.527
It's meant to overflow.

44:48.588 --> 44:50.229
It's meant to flow out.

44:52.051 --> 44:59.378
If you've ever come to the altar and had me pray for you, one of the things that I pray for is Lord, fill them to overflowing.

45:02.370 --> 45:04.873
Let your spirit flow out of them.

45:07.857 --> 45:14.606
Because when we live out our faith boldly trusting God, we become conduits of His hope and His healing.

45:14.886 --> 45:27.122
And we as a church, because we are filled with faith, because we are filled with the power of the Holy Spirit, we are out then out flowing of the hope and healing that we want to provide to our community.

45:32.130 --> 45:40.003
But all of this isn't just a tip, this isn't pastor preaching a message and we're gonna do this for a three month project and then we're gonna move on to something else.

45:40.584 --> 45:42.346
This is a life change.

45:42.407 --> 45:46.573
This is something that is a life long process and change.

45:47.635 --> 45:51.782
Our mission to offer hope and healing is an ongoing permanent effort.

45:52.002 --> 45:57.010
It requires us to continually renew our commitment to the Father and to each other.

46:01.538 --> 46:02.139
So we're gonna close.

46:02.880 --> 46:03.400
It's that time.

46:06.223 --> 46:08.045
We are, right?

46:09.487 --> 46:09.948
We are.

46:12.891 --> 46:16.875
We are an Assemblies of God Church.

46:16.895 --> 46:29.650
We individually are specifically church members, and we are called to provide hope and healing to our community, and we have a clear mission.

46:32.098 --> 46:39.039
To be able to provide, to be able to succeed in this mission, we need to anchor ourselves in God's presence.

46:41.045 --> 46:42.610
So I have some homework for you.

46:44.066 --> 46:51.354
I want you to make this week, I want you to make a priority to set aside time each day for prayer and reflection.

46:51.695 --> 46:56.700
Allow God's promises to be your anchor and let his peace guard your heart and mind.

46:56.741 --> 46:59.624
When fear arises, remember that you're not alone.

46:59.684 --> 47:07.032
God is with you guiding and protecting you and come to prayer meeting on Wednesday.

47:08.774 --> 47:12.018
Join us for a time of prayer.

47:12.738 --> 47:15.984
Second, we need to act courageously in our faith.

47:16.224 --> 47:21.113
We need to consider one area in your life where fear has held you back.

47:21.393 --> 47:27.003
It could be reaching out to a neighbor, volunteering at a community project, or standing up for what's right.

47:27.123 --> 47:32.172
Whatever it is, I want you to start looking for those opportunities.

47:33.174 --> 47:35.698
To take a step of faith this week

47:36.482 --> 47:44.554
Trusting that God's gonna give you everything you need to step out, encourage, and in faith, no matter what obstacles are in your way.

47:45.055 --> 47:50.543
And number three, to be a source of transformation in your community.

47:52.165 --> 47:53.868
We have to put feet to this.

47:54.709 --> 47:56.071
We have to put action.

47:57.173 --> 48:06.226
Think about how you can be light in a dark place, whether it's through a community outreach or offering a helping hand, or simply being present for someone in need.

48:06.850 --> 48:10.334
Let your faith inspire genuine change.

48:10.974 --> 48:17.482
Our community needs hope and healing that only Christ can bring, and we are His hands and feet.

48:19.464 --> 48:23.048
So let us, I want us to move forward as a church.

48:25.030 --> 48:36.402
I want us to move forward with confidence, not as people with fear, what's gonna happen tomorrow, what's gonna happen next month, but as a faith

48:36.610 --> 48:43.320
filled community ready to make a tangible difference in South City, St. Louis.

48:45.203 --> 48:46.145
Because here's why.

48:46.165 --> 48:49.930
Together we are, right?

48:50.711 --> 48:51.533
But what are we?

48:53.075 --> 49:01.408
We are the church and we will stand up and we will make known our Christ to a lost and dying world.

49:01.428 --> 49:05.554
We will be the church to offer hope and healing

49:07.778 --> 49:12.305
We are the church who is called to seek and to save the lost.

49:13.007 --> 49:13.507
Let's pray.

49:16.232 --> 49:17.334
So father, we praise you.

49:18.796 --> 49:19.477
We thank you.

49:20.739 --> 49:24.666
We lift up your name because your name is what is going to save our city.

49:25.026 --> 49:27.410
Your name is what is going to restore

49:27.490 --> 49:28.951
faith to our community.

49:29.031 --> 49:33.316
Your name is what's gonna bring unity again to Compton Heights.

49:33.576 --> 49:37.620
Your name is what is going to be covering all of South City.

49:37.920 --> 49:40.562
It is the name of Jesus that people will stand up.

49:40.843 --> 49:43.525
It is the name of Jesus that people will cry out.

49:43.786 --> 49:49.251
It is the name of Jesus that will offer hope and healing to their lives.

49:54.496 --> 49:56.818
As we close out today's service,

49:57.954 --> 49:59.516
every head bowed, every eye closed.

49:59.576 --> 50:06.104
I want to extend an invitation to anybody who feels the need for God's hope and healing in their life.

50:06.965 --> 50:13.272
Say pastor, you were talking about being in the storm and I'm being tossed to and fro.

50:17.077 --> 50:24.946
Whether you're facing fear, uncertainty, burdens of this world, know that God is here.

50:25.826 --> 50:28.310
know that He is ready to meet you where you are.

50:29.693 --> 50:37.847
Maybe you're struggling with fear about your health, feeling overwhelmed by financial worries, or facing the uncertainty of your relationships.

50:39.390 --> 50:43.878
Maybe the challenges of life have you feeling lost or burdened.

50:44.940 --> 50:50.770
Whatever the fear or struggle God is here, offering His peace, His strength, and His hope,

50:52.130 --> 50:57.872
For those that have never made a decision to follow Jesus today is the perfect time to open your heart to Him.

50:57.892 --> 51:02.610
God offers you forgiveness, peace, and a new beginning through His Son, Jesus.

51:03.234 --> 51:10.481
If you're ready to take that step, I wanna encourage you to come forward and we'll pray with you together as you begin this faith journey.

51:11.162 --> 51:26.057
For those who are already walking with Christ, if you need strength to face a specific fear, courage to take the next step or healing in an area of your life, whether it's physical, emotional, or spiritual, our altar is open for prayer.

51:27.198 --> 51:31.442
One of our pastoral folks, our prayer team leaders, are here to pray with you

51:31.874 --> 51:35.678
and to pray and believe for God's intervention and guidance in your life.

51:37.740 --> 51:49.312
So want us to take a moment to respond to what God has been speaking to us today, whether it's for salvation, whether it's prayer for a specific need, or simply a desire to draw closer to Him.

51:50.273 --> 51:51.414
Now is the time.

51:51.434 --> 51:58.021
God is here and He is ready to bring hope and healing and to transform your life.

51:58.141 --> 51:59.442
Please don't hesitate.

51:59.842 --> 52:06.801
As the choir sings our closing song, we'll simply be here to receive you if you need any kind of prayer.

52:07.282 --> 52:10.130
Amen and amen.

